## Project Overview
This project demonstrates core Object-Oriented Programming concepts in Java,
including encapsulation, constructors, methods, arrays of objects, and class
composition. The system manages students and courses while performing
calculations such as GPA averages and honors detection.

## Classes Description

### Student Class
The Student class stores personal and academic information such as name, ID,
major, GPA, and credits. It uses private fields with getters and setters to
ensure data encapsulation.

### Course Class
The Course class represents a university course and contains an array of
Student objects, demonstrating composition. It calculates average GPA and
identifies the student with the highest credits.

