## Reflection

In this project, I learned how to apply Object-Oriented Programming principles
in Java, such as creating classes, using constructors, methods, and working
with arrays of objects. I understood how encapsulation works by keeping fields
private and accessing them through getters and setters. This helped me better
organize the code and manage student data correctly. I also learned how to
calculate values like average GPA and find specific students using loops and conditions.

One of the main challenges was working with arrays of objects and making sure
indexes were handled correctly to avoid errors. Another challenge was
understanding how different classes interact with each other. However, this project
showed me the benefits of encapsulation and OOP principles, such as better
code readability, easier debugging, and improved maintainability.
Overall, this assignment helped me gain confidence in designing structured and clean Java programs.